### Code

I tried this code:

```rust
pub trait Trait<'p> {
    type Type;
}
impl<'p> Trait<'p> for str {
    type Type = &'p str;
}

pub trait Trait2 {
    fn foo<'p>(v: Self::Type)
    where
        Self: Trait<'p>;
}
impl Trait2 for str {
    fn foo<'p>(v: <Self as Trait<'p>>::Type)
    where
        Self: Trait<'p>,
    {
        let _s: &str = unsafe { std::mem::transmute(v) };
    }
}
```

I expected to see this happen: compiles, because `str::Type` is `&'p str`.

Instead, this happened: 
```
error[E0512]: cannot transmute between types of different sizes, or dependently-sized types
  --> src/lib.rs:19:32
   |
19 |         let s: &str = unsafe { std::mem::transmute(v) };
   |                                ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
   |
   = note: source type: `<str as Trait<'_>>::Type` (this type does not have a fixed size)
   = note: target type: `&str` (128 bits)
```

### Version it worked on

It most recently worked on: rust <= 1.68

### Version with regression

rust >= 1.69

`rustc --version --verbose`:
```
